le datasets in the field, and the popularity of this research area in recent years of publications and citations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":302,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/s11042-022-12153-2-1.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/s11042-022-12153-2-1.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"Application_of_game\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-eb8bb7cc-5854-4642-adad-c4ee47ab6e09\" href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/s11042-022-12153-2-1.pdf\">Application_of_game</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/s11042-022-12153-2-1.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-eb8bb7cc-5854-4642-adad-c4ee47ab6e09\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','Applications of game theory in deep learning: a survey','','inherit','closed','closed','','301-revision-v1','','','2024-03-05 11:29:39','2024-03-05 11:29:39','',301,'http://localhost/?p=303',0,'revision','',0),(304,1,'2024-03-05 11:32:53','2024-03-05 11:32:53','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>June 2022</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>by Pham Duc Anh Ta, Hong Nhung Nguyen, Thi Nga Nguyen</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, the competition between students when applying for credit on campus has become a rather persistent issue for both the student and universities. Network congestion, the lack of slots in a class, and the cancellation of a class after successful enrollment have led to the fact that students often graduate late or disrupt the registration plan of a semester. Considering that this dilemma requires a balance of benefits for thousands of people, in this case, all the students of a university, this paper aims to solve it using game theory, a branch of mathematics that deals with finding optimal strategies in competitive situations, which relies heavily on the concepts of strategy, opponent modeling, and equilibrium. To find a solution to this issue, we will apply the GDE3 Algorithm because, with our game theory-based registration system, credit registration becomes seamless and painless by incentivizing the students with rewards they will gain upon meeting some conditions. This research provides both students and universities with the optimal solution for successful credit registration in the future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":298,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-67c2dfd1-a26d-4dd2-9d84-9cc1cd664313\" href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm.pdf\">Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-67c2dfd1-a26d-4dd2-9d84-9cc1cd664313\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','UTILIZE GAME THEORY TO PARTICIPATEIN ACADEMIC COURSES IN UNIVERSITY BYGD3 ALGORITHM','','publish','open','open','','utilize-game-theory-to-participatein-academic-courses-in-university-bygd3-algorithm','','','2024-03-05 11:45:53','2024-03-05 11:45:53','',0,'http://localhost/?p=304',0,'post','',0),(305,1,'2024-03-05 11:32:53','2024-03-05 11:32:53','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>June 2022</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>by Pham Duc Anh Ta, Hong Nhung Nguyen, Thi Nga Nguyen</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, the competition between students when applying for credit on campus has become a rather persistent issue for both the student and universities. Network congestion, the lack of slots in a class, and the cancellation of a class after successful enrollment have led to the fact that students often graduate late or disrupt the registration plan of a semester. Considering that this dilemma requires a balance of benefits for thousands of people, in this case, all the students of a university, this paper aims to solve it using game theory, a branch of mathematics that deals with finding optimal strategies in competitive situations, which relies heavily on the concepts of strategy, opponent modeling, and equilibrium. To find a solution to this issue, we will apply the GDE3 Algorithm because, with our game theory-based registration system, credit registration becomes seamless and painless by incentivizing the students with rewards they will gain upon meeting some conditions. This research provides both students and universities with the optimal solution for successful credit registration in the future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":298,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-67c2dfd1-a26d-4dd2-9d84-9cc1cd664313\" href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm.pdf\">Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Utilize_Game_Theory_to_participate_in__academic_courses_in_universities_by_GD3_Algorithm.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-67c2dfd1-a26d-4dd2-9d84-9cc1cd664313\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','UTILIZE GAME THEORY TO PARTICIPATEIN ACADEMIC COURSES IN UNIVERSITY BYGD3 ALGORITHM','','inherit','closed','closed','','304-revision-v1','','','2024-03-05 11:32:53','2024-03-05 11:32:53','',304,'http://localhost/?p=305',0,'revision','',0),(306,1,'2024-03-05 11:38:09','2024-03-05 11:38:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Year: Spring 2022</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br><strong>Instructor: Dr. Trinh Bao Ngoc</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Students: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Thi Thanh Huyen</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Duy Anh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Vu Thi Bich Phuong</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Can Thi Mai Anh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Thi Diem Quynh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cooperation between countries and different economies is an inevitable trend for development in all aspects, but contradictions and trading conflicts still exist even though they have been resolved by many methods. This article suggests the use of game theory to resolve conflicts of economic cooperation between countries in the WTO participating in global cooperation. Therefore, the purpose of using game theory is to understand and analyze the behaviour or decisions of global cooperative countries that are one the typical cases of conflict situations. Based on the FEMO [1] algorithm model, it will show the main tensions when cooperating based on trade and protectionist principles, and point out common causes leading to domestic conflicts and conflicts when cooperating between countries families. From there, we came up with issues that need to be resolved including unfair competition between economic cooperation partners, the need to use domestic goods and taxes caused by the trade war to minimize failures, aim to solve problems and offer some strategic choices for players who use game theory joining the world trade market.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":296,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"SS207_Monday\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-dd403067-6ac5-40e5-aef8-cd1bccae366a\" href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\">SS207_Monday</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-dd403067-6ac5-40e5-aef8-cd1bccae366a\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','Application of Game Theory in trading conflictresolution of global cooperation in economicsbetween member countries in WTO using FairEvolutionary Multiobjective Optimizer (FEMO)','','publish','open','open','','application-of-game-theory-in-trading-conflictresolution-of-global-cooperation-in-economicsbetween-member-countries-in-wto-using-fairevolutionary-multiobjective-optimizer-femo','','','2024-03-05 11:45:27','2024-03-05 11:45:27','',0,'http://localhost/?p=306',0,'post','',0),(307,1,'2024-03-05 11:38:09','2024-03-05 11:38:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Year: Spring 2022</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br><strong>Instructor: Ph.D Trinh Bao Ngoc</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Students: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Thi Thanh Huyen</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Duy Anh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Vu Thi Bich Phuong</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Can Thi Mai Anh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Thi Diem Quynh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cooperation between countries and different economies is an inevitable trend for development in all aspects, but contradictions and trading conflicts still exist even though they have been resolved by many methods. This article suggests the use of game theory to resolve conflicts of economic cooperation between countries in the WTO participating in global cooperation. Therefore, the purpose of using game theory is to understand and analyze the behaviour or decisions of global cooperative countries that are one the typical cases of conflict situations. Based on the FEMO [1] algorithm model, it will show the main tensions when cooperating based on trade and protectionist principles, and point out common causes leading to domestic conflicts and conflicts when cooperating between countries families. From there, we came up with issues that need to be resolved including unfair competition between economic cooperation partners, the need to use domestic goods and taxes caused by the trade war to minimize failures, aim to solve problems and offer some strategic choices for players who use game theory joining the world trade market.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":296,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"SS207_Monday\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-dd403067-6ac5-40e5-aef8-cd1bccae366a\" href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\">SS207_Monday</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-dd403067-6ac5-40e5-aef8-cd1bccae366a\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','Application of Game Theory in trading conflictresolution of global cooperation in economicsbetween member countries in WTO using FairEvolutionary Multiobjective Optimizer (FEMO)','','inherit','closed','closed','','306-revision-v1','','','2024-03-05 11:38:09','2024-03-05 11:38:09','',306,'http://localhost/?p=307',0,'revision','',0),(308,1,'2024-03-05 11:40:04','2024-03-05 11:40:04','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>July 22, 2022</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>by Pham Quang Ha, Nguyen Trung Kien, Tran Duong Son, Nguyen To Uyen, Vu Hong Van</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When emergencies such as natural disasters or pandemics happen, it is clear that effective decision-making is critical for equitable and optimal allocation of resources. If there are more demands than resources available, it will cause many conflicts between emergency centers such as how to respond equally to locations or conflicts between allocation decision-makers. To solve that problem, we provided an alternate instruction to existing balanced resource allocation processes using Game theory. In this paper, the ideal model that we selected is the Unified Game-based model. Based on Game theory, this research proposes a non-cooperative game model for resource allocation and provides algorithms to compute Nash equilibrium. With the application of Game theory, when Nash equilibrium occurs, each player obtains an optimal strategy that leads to an efficient allocation after considering the opponents strategy. Additionally, the Non-dominated Sorting Genetic Algorithm (NSGA-II) is also applied. Using a particular kind of crossover and mutation to create children, this algorithm then selects the following generation using comparisons of crowding distance and nondominated-sorting. The experimental results of this study show the possibility of optimizing resource allocation for emergency management sites. Keywords: Game theory, Nash equilibrium, Unified Game-based Model, NSGA-II algorithm. Keywords: Game theory, Nash equilibrium, Unified Game-based Model, NSGA-II algorithm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":297,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/The-application-of-Game-Theory-and-NSGA-II.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2